         <div type="researchScenario">
            <head type="scenarioTitle" xml:lang="en">
                    TARGET: Building a translational Greek corpus
                </head>
            <desc type="definition" xml:lang="en">
                    This scenario explains the steps to take to compile an annotated translational corpus in order to conduct linguistic and statistical analysis based on it. The first step is to collect written texts translated into Greek from a variety of source languages, European and non-European. The next step is to annotate the data and put the annotated corpus into a corpus query engine to query and analyze it based on its annotations. 
                </desc>
